  "examples": {
    "crystal_shard": {
      "subject-first": [
        "Torga the orc faced Grock the goblin with open contempt.",
        "Their respective tribes had been warring for \nmany years, as long as any living member of either group could remember.",
        "They shared a valley in the \nSpine of the World and competed for ground and food with the brutality indicative of their warlike races."
      ],
      "adverbial-first": [
        "In any other place, at any other time, the tribes could never have \nbeen this close without joining in fierce battle.",
        "Thus Crenshinibon exerted its will through manipulation, insinuating illusions of conquest into the wizard's dreams, allowing Kessell to view the possibilities of power.",
        "With the relic close to his heart, he could become the conqueror; he could make people, even the wizards in the Hosttower, tremble at the mere mention of his name."
      ],
      "participial-first": [
        "Flanked by his trolls, the wizard was waiting for Errtu in Cryshal-Tirith's main chamber, the tower's first \nlevel.",
        "Brimming with confidence, he addressed the demon again, \nthis time a stern edge in his voice.",
        "Finding an appropriate clearing, he hastily set up a \nsmall campsite."
      ],
      "conjunction-first": [
        "And now they stood on common ground with no weapons drawn, compelled to this spot by a force even \ngreater than their hatred for each other.",
        "But now, they had to be content with idle threats and \ndangerous glares, for they had been commanded to put aside their differences.",
        "But his crowning achievement was a group of frost giants that had simply wandered in, desiring only to please the wielder of Crenshinibon."
      ],
      "dialogue-first": [
        "\"Akar Kessell!\" he shouted to the harem girl that manicured his long fingernails as he sat in contemplation, though the girl's mind had long ago been destroyed by Crenshinibon.",
        "\"All glory to the Tyrant of Icewind Dale!\"",
        "\"Errtu!\" the young man called, the words forced from him by the demands of the spell."
      ],
      "interjection-first": [
        "What was it you said?\" \nWulfgar laughed heartily.",
        "Bah!",
        "What terrible fate would his mighty mentor impose upon him for his betrayal?"
      ],
      "other": [
        "Be wary of that day, son, for ye'll put a great deal of \nyerself into that weapon.",
        ".",
        ".\" He let his voice trail away, and he looked back longingly to the emptiness of the open \ntundra beyond Kelvin's Cairn."
      ]
    },
    "streams_of_silver": {
      "subject-first": [
        "The sun beamed brightly on the morning of the first day out from Longsaddle.",
        "The companions, refreshed by their visit with the Harpells, rode at a strong pace, but still managed to enjoy the clear weather and the clear road.",
        "The land was flat and unmarked, not a tree or hill anywhere near."
      ],
      "adverbial-first": [
        "However pleasant the morning might seem to them, he knew they were still in the wilds.",
        "By the time they broke for lunch, a high haze veiled the sunshine.",
        "In the wild, even the weather proved an enemy."
      ],
      "participial-first": [
        "Following the beacon of his whistles, Drizzt and Bruenor soon found him.",
        "Thinking the dwarf about to expire, Drizzt could not refuse.",
        "Thinking quickly, the drow went to an alternate attack, using his ineffective blades to parry the clubbing limbs."
      ],
      "conjunction-first": [
        "But a careful place.",
        "But they plodded on through the deepening mud.",
        "As if in prideful reply, a lightning bolt exploded just a few yards to the side of the riders."
      ],
      "dialogue-first": [
        "\"Three days to Nesmé, maybe four,\" Regis told them.",
        "\"More to three if the weather holds,\" said Wulfgar.",
        "\"What do ye know of this place, Nesmé?\" Bruenor asked Regis."
      ],
      "interjection-first": [
        "Damn their town.",
        "No single architectural style dominated Silverymoon, unless it was the freedom of a builder to exercise his or her personal creativity without fear of judgement or scorn.",
        "No longer seeking only to flee, he began looking for a defensible piece of ground."
      ],
      "other": [
        "Might it be his love of ankle-deep mud that sucks his little legs in to the knees?\"\n\nBruenor stopped laughing and studied the halfling's reaction to the drow's questions.",
        "Be gone and never return to our lands.\"\n\n\"We go where we choose,\" snarled Bruenor.",
        "May the river wash it away!\" He turned to his friends."
      ]
    },
    "halflings_gem": {
      "subject-first": [
        "The halfling hung by his ankles, suspended upside down with chains above a cauldron of\nboiling liquid.",
        "Not water, though, but something darker.",
        "A red hue, perhaps."
      ],
      "adverbial-first": [
        "There was a pause in the descent.",
        "Then the evil voice laughed one final time.",
        "Over the course of the\nlast decade, four very special companions had come into his life, not one of them a dwarf."
      ],
      "participial-first": [
        "Struggling with all his might, he managed to bring the chariot up a few more feet and level it off.",
        "Using a common merchant's trick, Deudermont closed in on a vessel and shadowed its course, keeping the Sea Sprite in its wake.",
        "Meaning to join his friend, he rushed the five remaining pirates on the plank."
      ],
      "conjunction-first": [
        "But no screams could be heard.",
        "But to Bruenor's eyes, all was not as it should be.",
        "But Bruenor had wandered through the last few days absently, playing a role thrust upon\nhim before he could truly appreciate it."
      ],
      "dialogue-first": [
        "\"Another one?\" came a soft call from the door.",
        "\"About Regis again?\" asked Catti-brie, moving closer.",
        "\"Rumblebelly,\" Bruenor softly corrected, using the nickname he had tagged on the\nhalfling who had been his closest friend for nearly a decade."
      ],
      "interjection-first": [
        "Alas, all he could see was the reflection of the candlelit room,\nthe crown and armor of the king of Mithril Hall.",
        "No one here has ever.",
        "No stinkin' assassin's going to put an end to\nRumblebelly!\" He clenched the drow's arm tightly one final time and turned to Wulfgar, the\nlad he had ushered into manhood."
      ],
      "other": [
        ".",
        "uh, maybe,\" Harkle proclaimed as confidently as he could.",
        "."
      ]
    }
  }
